content.text:
I'm glad you're interested in uplifting news! Here are some positive stories from recent times:

- **12-Year-Old Girl Plants 150,000 Trees in India**: A young environmentalist in India has led a massive reforestation effort, planting 150,000 trees to combat deforestation and climate change. ([goodnewsnetwork.org](https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/?utm_source=openai))

- **China Achieves 'Excellent' Water Quality in 90% of Rivers and Lakes**: China has reported that 90% of its rivers and lakes now meet 'excellent' water quality standards, marking a significant environmental achievement. ([goodnewsnetwork.org](https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/?utm_source=openai))

- **Yurok Tribe Celebrates Return of Ancestral Homelands**: The Yurok Tribe in the United States has successfully reclaimed portions of their ancestral lands, a significant step in preserving their cultural heritage. ([goodnewsnetwork.org](https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/?utm_source=openai))

- **90-Year-Old Great-Grandmother Earns Associate Art Degree**: Rita Hernandez, a 90-year-old great-grandmother, graduated with an associate art degree, showcasing that it's never too late to pursue education. ([abcnews.go.com](https://abcnews.go.com/alerts/goodnews?utm_source=openai))

- **Service Dog Honored at College Graduation**: Canela, a service dog, was honored alongside her owner at Rollins College's graduation ceremony, recognizing her support throughout her owner's academic journey. ([abcnews.go.com](https://abcnews.go.com/alerts/goodnews?utm_source=openai))

I hope these stories bring a smile to your day!
